# Org Layout Restructure: Onboard Flow + Header Extraction

## Context

The `[slug]/layout.tsx` currently has a conditional early return that renders `<GitHubBindStep>` as a full-screen UI with NO sidebar and NO header when GitHub binding is missing. This is architecturally problematic:
1. The onboard step bypasses the org shell entirely — no way to switch teams or access docs during setup
2. `TeamSwitcher` is coupled inside `AppSidebar` instead of being an always-visible org-level element
3. No route-based onboard flow makes it hard to add future setup steps

**Goal**: Replace the conditional render with a redirect to `/[slug]/onboard`, extract the header (TeamSwitcher + AppHeader) to be always-visible on org routes, and create a multi-step onboard route.

## Current State

**Route tree**: `[slug]/layout.tsx` → org access + binding check + sidebar shell
```
[slug]/
  layout.tsx     ← does everything: org access, binding check, sidebar shell, or GitHubBindStep
  page.tsx       ← Explore page
  _components/   ← mailbox components
  (manage)/      ← entities, events, jobs, settings, sources
```

**Layout rendering** (`layout.tsx:41-89`):
- `requireOrgAccess(slug)` → org membership check
- `getGitHubBinding(org.id)` → if no active binding → `return <GitHubBindStep />` (no header, no sidebar)
- If active → full shell: `SidebarProvider > AppSidebar + (header + SidebarInset)`

**Key components**:
- `AppSidebar` (`components/app-sidebar.tsx`): Client component. Fetches organizations via tRPC. Renders TeamSwitcher + Search in h-14 header, nav items, footer. Uses `<Sidebar collapsible="offcanvas" variant="inset">`
- `AppHeader` (`components/app-header.tsx`): Client component. Fetches account profile. Renders Docs, API Reference, UserMenu
- `TeamSwitcher` (`packages/ui/.../team-switcher.tsx`): Pure UI component (no data fetching). Props: organizations, mode, onOrgSelect, createTeamHref
- `Sidebar` desktop: `position: fixed; inset-y-0; h-svh; w-[--sidebar-width]` — full viewport height. `className` prop applied to this fixed container (line 239). Mobile: Sheet drawer (className NOT applied)

## Desired End State

### Desktop (workspace)
```
┌────────────┬─────────────────────────────────────┐
│ [Acme ▾] 🔍│           Docs  API Reference  [JD] │  ← h-14 header (always visible)
├────────────┼─────────────────────────────────────┤
│ Explore    │ ┌─────────────────────────────────┐ │
│ Entities   │ │  SidebarInset (rounded card)    │ │
│ ────────── │ │  {page content}                 │ │
│ Events     │ │                                 │ │
│ Sources    │ └─────────────────────────────────┘ │
│ Jobs       │                                     │
│ Settings   │                                     │
└────────────┴─────────────────────────────────────┘
  ↑ sidebar column         ↑ inset column
  w = --sidebar-width      w = flex-1
```

### Mobile (workspace)
- Header: `[☰ hamburger]  Docs  API  [JD]` — no TeamSwitcher
- Sidebar Sheet: `[TeamSwitcher + 🔍] + nav items` — TeamSwitcher in sheet

### Desktop/Mobile (onboard)
```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│ [Acme ▾]              Docs  API Reference  [JD] │  ← header (always visible, all viewports)
├─────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│                                                 │
│       Setting up Acme                           │
│       ✓ Create team                             │
│       ● Connect GitHub                          │
│       [Connect GitHub]                          │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

### Route structure after
```
[slug]/
  layout.tsx                ← org access + error boundary only
  (workspace)/
    layout.tsx              ← binding check + redirect, SidebarProvider shell with header
    page.tsx                ← (moved) Explore page
    _components/            ← (moved) mailbox components
    (manage)/               ← (moved) entities, events, jobs, settings, sources
  onboard/
    layout.tsx              ← standalone header (TeamSwitcher + AppHeader), no sidebar
    page.tsx                ← redirect to current step
    github/
      page.tsx              ← GitHub connect step
```

## What We're NOT Doing

- Modifying the `Sidebar` primitive in `packages/ui/` — we use className overrides only
- Changing the mobile sidebar Sheet behavior — stays as-is
- Adding actual onboard steps beyond GitHub — just the multi-step route structure
- Merging `AppHeader` into a single component — it stays separate for reuse
- Changing the `(manage)/` layout or any child routes — only their parent changes

---

## Phase 1: Foundation — Route Group + Cache

No visual changes. Structural refactor to introduce `(workspace)` route group.

### 1.1 Wrap `requireOrgAccess` with `React.cache()`

**File**: `apps/app/src/lib/org-access-clerk.ts`

`getGitHubBinding` already uses `cache()` (confirmed at `lib/github-binding.ts:3-5`). Apply the same pattern to `requireOrgAccess` so it dedupes across `[slug]/layout.tsx` and child layouts within the same request.

```ts
import { cache } from "react";

export const requireOrgAccess = cache(async function requireOrgAccess(
  slug: string
): Promise<OrgWithAccess> {
  // ... existing implementation unchanged ...
});
```

### 1.2 Create `(workspace)` route group and move files

Use `git mv` for history preservation:

```bash
mkdir -p apps/app/src/app/\(app\)/\(org\)/\[slug\]/\(workspace\)
git mv apps/app/src/app/\(app\)/\(org\)/\[slug\]/page.tsx \
       apps/app/src/app/\(app\)/\(org\)/\[slug\]/\(workspace\)/page.tsx
git mv apps/app/src/app/\(app\)/\(org\)/\[slug\]/_components \
       apps/app/src/app/\(app\)/\(org\)/\[slug\]/\(workspace\)/_components
git mv apps/app/src/app/\(app\)/\(org\)/\[slug\]/\(manage\) \
       apps/app/src/app/\(app\)/\(org\)/\[slug\]/\(workspace\)/\(manage\)
```

Relative imports in `page.tsx` → `./_components/mailbox` remain valid since both moved together.

### 1.3 Create `(workspace)/layout.tsx` — pass-through initially

**File**: NEW at `[slug]/(workspace)/layout.tsx`

Initially a thin pass-through that extracts the sidebar shell from the old layout. This preserves current behavior.

```tsx
import { HydrateClient } from "@repo/app-trpc/server";
import { SidebarInset, SidebarProvider, SidebarTrigger } from "@repo/ui/components/ui/sidebar";
import { Loader2 } from "lucide-react";
import { redirect } from "next/navigation";
import { Suspense } from "react";
import { AppHeader } from "~/components/app-header";
import { AppSidebar } from "~/components/app-sidebar";
import { CommandPalette } from "~/components/command-palette";
import { getGitHubBinding } from "~/lib/github-binding";
import { requireOrgAccess } from "~/lib/org-access-clerk";

interface WorkspaceLayoutProps {
  children: React.ReactNode;
  params: Promise<{ slug: string }>;
}

export default async function WorkspaceLayout({ children, params }: WorkspaceLayoutProps) {
  const { slug } = await params;
  const { org } = await requireOrgAccess(slug); // cache()'d — free

  const binding = await getGitHubBinding(org.id);
  if (!binding || binding.status !== "active") {
    redirect(`/${slug}/onboard`);
  }

  return (
    <HydrateClient>
      <SidebarProvider className="!h-full !min-h-0 overflow-hidden bg-sidebar">
        <AppSidebar />
        <CommandPalette />
        <div className="flex min-h-0 flex-1 flex-col overflow-hidden lg:pr-2 lg:pb-2">
          <div className="flex h-14 shrink-0 items-center px-4">
            <SidebarTrigger className="lg:hidden" />
            <Suspense fallback={<div className="h-8 w-8" />}>
              <AppHeader />
            </Suspense>
          </div>
          <SidebarInset className="overflow-hidden lg:rounded-xl lg:shadow-sm">
            <Suspense fallback={<PageLoadingSkeleton />}>{children}</Suspense>
          </SidebarInset>
        </div>
      </SidebarProvider>
    </HydrateClient>
  );
}

function PageLoadingSkeleton() {
  return (
    <div className="flex h-full min-h-0 w-full items-center justify-center">
      <Loader2 className="h-8 w-8 animate-spin text-muted-foreground" />
    </div>
  );
}
```

### 1.4 Slim down `[slug]/layout.tsx`

**File**: `apps/app/src/app/(app)/(org)/[slug]/layout.tsx`

Strip to org access + error boundary only:

```tsx
import { parseError } from "@vendor/observability/error/next";
import { log } from "@vendor/observability/log/next";
import { notFound } from "next/navigation";
import { OrgPageErrorBoundary } from "~/components/errors/org-page-error-boundary";
import { requireOrgAccess } from "~/lib/org-access-clerk";

interface OrgLayoutProps {
  children: React.ReactNode;
  params: Promise<{ slug: string }>;
}

export default async function OrgLayout({ children, params }: OrgLayoutProps) {
  const { slug } = await params;

  try {
    await requireOrgAccess(slug);
  } catch (error) {
    log.debug("[org-layout] access denied", { slug, error: parseError(error) });
    notFound();
  }

  return <OrgPageErrorBoundary orgSlug={slug}>{children}</OrgPageErrorBoundary>;
}
```

### Success Criteria — Phase 1

#### Automated:
- [ ] `pnpm check` passes (no lint/type errors from moved files)
- [ ] `pnpm typecheck` passes
- [ ] `pnpm build:app` succeeds

#### Manual:
- [ ] All existing org routes (`/[slug]`, `/[slug]/entities`, `/[slug]/settings`, etc.) work identically
- [ ] Sidebar, nav, header unchanged visually
- [ ] Orgs without GitHub binding now get redirected (404 since onboard route doesn't exist yet — expected)

---

## Phase 2: Onboard Route

### 2.1 Rename `GitHubBindStep` → `GitHubConnectStep`

**File**: `apps/app/src/components/github-bind-step.tsx` → rename to `github-connect-step.tsx`

Changes:
- Add `orgSlug` prop
- On success: `router.push(`/${orgSlug}`)` instead of `router.refresh()`
- Component renamed to `GitHubConnectStep`

```tsx
interface GitHubConnectStepProps {
  orgName: string;
  orgSlug: string;
}

export function GitHubConnectStep({ orgName, orgSlug }: GitHubConnectStepProps) {
  // ... existing hooks ...
  const { handleConnect, isConnecting } = useOAuthPopup({
    provider: "github",
